ilable to humans and halflings (I think.)  I don't really want to roleplay a human but I don't know if I could put up with the other halflings.  I don't mean any disrespect to the halfling community and agree that I'm way too fanatical about the proper behavior of halflings <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>On other servers a majority of the halfling players seem to be the ones that chose the race because of the leveling bonus, or their stats, and not a true interest in that race.  (I feel this way about gnomes as well, that's why a gnome paladin appeals to me, people will know that I didn't pick the race because of their stats or special attributes.  Because most interaction in EverQuest is brief and it takes a while to get to know a specific character, I guess I'm worried about what the other person thinks about who I am.  You haven't avoided a certain race or class because of previous encounters with members of that race or class?) <br><br>If I'm this worried about race should I just go with gnomes?  I like halflings too though and it would be fun playing a Karana worshipping halfling.<br><br>What is the situation on Firiona Vie?  On Sullon Zek I made great friends and thought nothing of my choice to be a dwarf, I just like the Butcherblock zone, until a guildmate I'd hunted with several times before mentioned something like:  &quot;Sorry I couldn't help you with that quest earlier, Most of the dwarves I meet are impatient and I didn't really need to deal with any of that today.&quot; <p>Fork, 29 Paladin of Sullon Zek < Divine Essence >,  Retired</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 507<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 